  "text": "## HTTP Health Check Endpoint Implementations Across Go Projects\n\n### Kubernetes (/healthz and /readyz)\n\nKubernetes implements health check endpoints through the apiserver health check system in `staging/src/k8s.io/apiserver/pkg/server/healthz/`. The framework provides:\n\n**Main Functions:**\n- `InstallHandler()`: Registers handlers for the `/healthz` endpoint (deprecated as of v1.16)\n- `InstallReadyzHandler()`: Registers handlers for the `/readyz` readiness endpoint  \n- `InstallLivezHandler()`: Registers handlers for the `/livez` liveness endpoint\n- `AddBootSequenceHealthChecks()`: Adds checks for boot sequence initialization\n\n**Health Checkers Implemented:**\n- `PingHealthz`: Basic availability check that always returns healthy\n- `LogHealthz`: Verifies logging subsystem is functional\n- `NewInformerSyncHealthz`: Checks that informers have synced from etcd\n\n**Dependency Checks:**\n- **etcd database connectivity**: Via `/healthz/etcd` to verify control plane data store\n- **informer synchronization**: Ensures all cached informers have synced from etcd\n- **logging system**: Verifies logging is not blocked\n- **boot hooks**: Checks for post-start hooks including RBAC bootstrap, admission initialization\n\nReadyz health checks have no grace period and fail until boot completes, while livez checks have configurable grace periods via `--livez-grace-period` flag.\n\n### Grafana (/healthz)\n\nGrafana implements health check endpoints registered in `pkg/api/api.go`. The `/healthz` endpoint was introduced (v7.2.0) as a lightweight liveness probe distinct from `/api/health`:\n\n**Implementation Details:**\n- `/healthz`: Lightweight liveness check that returns 200 OK without database access requirement\n- `/api/health`: Separate endpoint requiring database connectivity, checking full system health\n- Health check endpoints bypass middleware processing to work independently of authentication\n\n**Dependency Checks:**\n- `/healthz`: Basic process liveness (no dependencies)\n- `/api/health`: Database connectivity, service dependencies\n\n### Prometheus (/healthz and /readyz)\n\nPrometheus implements health check endpoints in `web/web.go` with state management in `cmd/prometheus/main.go`:\n\n**Endpoints:**\n- `/-/healthy`: Liveness probe indicating process is running (always 200 until shutdown)\n- `/-/ready`: Readiness probe returning 200 only when ready to serve queries\n\n**Main Components:**\n- `Handler` struct: Contains `ready` atomic uint32 field to track readiness state\n- `Register()` method: Registers routes for both health endpoints\n- `Ready` middleware: Applied to all routes except `/-/healthy`, enforces readiness checks\n\n**Dependency Checks:**\n- **TSDB initialization**: Checks storage engine and WAL replay completion\n- **query readiness**: Verifies Prometheus can respond to queries after recovery\n- **startup sequence**: Server starts in non-ready state, transitions to ready after config loading and WAL recovery complete\n\n### Comparison Summary\n\n**Kubernetes** provides the most comprehensive health checking framework with pluggable HealthChecker interface supporting multiple boot-time and runtime checks including etcd, logging, and informer synchronization.\n\n**Grafana** separates liveness (`/healthz`) from full health (`/api/health`), with the lightweight liveness probe designed to bypass middleware and database dependencies.\n\n**Prometheus** implements both liveness and readiness with atomic state management, making readiness state explicitly trackable and allowing deferred initialization before accepting traffic.\n\nAll three projects distinguish between liveness (process alive) and readiness (ready to serve traffic), with Kubernetes and Prometheus implementing separate endpoints while Grafana additionally separates database-dependent checks.\n\n### Source References\n\n- [Kubernetes API health endpoints](https://kubernetes.io/docs/reference/using-api/health-checks/)\n- [Kubernetes healthz.go implementation](https://github.com/kubernetes/kubernetes/blob/master/staging/src/k8s.io/apiserver/pkg/server/healthz/healthz.go)\n- [Grafana healthz endpoint PR #27536](https://github.com/grafana/grafana/pull/27536)\n- [Prometheus health endpoints PR #2997](https://github.com/prometheus/prometheus/pull/2997)\n- [Prometheus web/web.go](https://github.com/prometheus/prometheus/blob/main/web/web.go)\n"
